[
  {
    "text": "Terra Scientific Pipelines Service (Teaspoons) is not limited to pipelines that require proprietary data inaccessible to users; it is used whenever a user cannot run a pipeline directly in Terra, which may include missing computational resources, software dependencies, or access to any required data, proprietary or not.",
    "topic": "Service scope"
  },
  {
    "text": "When a pipeline uses proprietary data as a reference panel (e.g., for imputation), the service still falls under the condition that the user cannot access that proprietary data directly; the service runs the pipeline on their behalf without granting them direct access to the underlying reference data.",
    "topic": "Reference panel use case"
  },
  {
    "text": "The service never exposes proprietary data, including reference panels, to the end user; it only returns the pipeline outputs that the user is authorized to see.",
    "topic": "Data exposure"
  }
]
